quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say<a class="sup"><sup>sg </sup></a>, “It was revealed to me that a band of unseen beings{1}listened in and said, ‘Indeed, we have heard a wondrous Recital{2}",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>jinn</i> which are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.],footnotes:2:[The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an</i> which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
  72,2,"that guides to prudence, so we have come to believe in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord."
  72,3,"<span class="h">And that{1}</span>most high is the Grandeur of our Lord—He never took a female companion nor a child.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn ‘Amer, Abu Ja’far, Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “And indeed…”</span>
  72,4,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>our fool used to speak untruthfully about Allah."
  72,5,"<span class="h">And that{1}</span>we thought that humans and unseen beings would never <span class="h">say{2}</span><span class=""h"">a lie about</span>Allah.",footnotes:1:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn ‘Amer, Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “And indeed…”</span>],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…would never attribute a lie to Allah.”</span>]
  72,6,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>certain men among humans used to seek refuge in certain men among the unseen beings, but they only increased them in confusion."
  72,7,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>they thought, as you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>thought, that Allah would never resurrect anyone."
  72,8,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>we sought to reach the heaven and found it filled with stern guards and meteors."
  72,9,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>we used to take up positions to listen in, but whoever listens now finds a meteor in wait for him."
  72,10,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>we do not know whether ill has been desired for those on earth, or if their Lord has desired prudence for them."
